This paper presents a method for generalizing value function estimation over timescale, which is a common problem in reinforcement learning and control. The paper uses linear function approximation and deep reinforcement learning to evaluate the proposed method, which suggests that it could be relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. Based on the content of the paper, the most likely sub-categories are machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV).
